context: New York City traces its roots to its <a5_0>1624<a5_0/> founding as a trading post by colonists of <a1_0>the Dutch Republic<a1_0/> and was named <a0_0>New Amsterdam<a0_0/> in <a6_0>1626<a6_0/>. The city and its surroundings came under English control in <a3_0><a7_0>1664<a7_0/><a3_0/>. New York served as the capital of the United States from 1785 until <a2_0><a4_0><a8_0>1790<a8_0/><a4_0/><a2_0/>. It has been the country's largest city since 1790. The Statue of Liberty greeted millions of immigrants as they came to the Americas by ship in the late 19th and early 20th centuries and is a globally recognized symbol of the United States and its democracy.
